Here is the complete catalog of every Result/Either/error-as-value pattern found across the codebase.

---

## Pattern Examples: Result-Type and Error-As-Value Patterns

---

### Pattern 1: Custom `Result<T, E>` type — `{ ok: true; value: T } | { ok: false; error: E }`

**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/core/ai-sdk/src/core/server/result.ts`
**Used for**: AI SDK runtime — session validation, message processing

The type and all combinators are defined here:

```ts
export type Result<T, E = Error> =
  | { ok: true; value: T }
  | { ok: false; error: E };

export const Ok = <T>(value: T): Result<T, never> => ({ ok: true, value });
export const Err = <E>(error: E): Result<never, E> => ({ ok: false, error });

export function mapResult<T, U, E>(result: Result<T, E>, fn: (value: T) => U): Result<U, E>
export function andThen<T, U, E>(result: Result<T, E>, fn: (value: T) => Result<U, E>): Result<U, E>
export function mapError<T, E, F>(result: Result<T, E>, fn: (error: E) => F): Result<T, F>
export function unwrapOr<T, E>(result: Result<T, E>, defaultValue: T): T
export function allOk<T, E>(results: Result<T, E>[]): results is { ok: true; value: T }[]
export function collect<T, E>(results: Result<T, E>[]): Result<T[], E>
```

**Consumed in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/core/ai-sdk/src/core/server/runtime.ts:31-32`

```ts
import type { Result } from "./result";
import { Err, Ok } from "./result";

export async function validateSession(...): Promise<Result<ValidatedSession, ApiError>> {
  // ...
  return Ok({ exists: false });
  return Err(new SessionForbiddenError());
}

export async function processMessage(...): Promise<Result<ProcessMessagesResult<TMessage>, ApiError>> {
  // ...
  return Err(new NoUserMessageError());
  return Ok({ allMessages, recentUserMessage: message });
}
```

**Test coverage**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/core/ai-sdk/src/core/server/result.test.ts` — full coverage of `Ok`, `Err`, `mapResult`, `andThen`, `mapError`, `unwrapOr`, `collect`, and async `Result` composition.

---

### Pattern 2: `neverthrow` library — `Result<T, E>` with `.match()`

**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/packages/app-config/src/parse.ts`
**Installed in**: `packages/app-config/package.json` — `"neverthrow": "catalog:"` (catalog version `^8.2.0` in `pnpm-workspace.yaml:47`)

```ts
import type { Result } from "neverthrow";
import { err, ok } from "neverthrow";

export async function loadConfig(repoPath: string): Promise<Result<LightfastConfig, ConfigError>> {
  // ...
  return err(new ConfigError(`...`, "FILE_NOT_FOUND", error));
  return err(new ConfigError(`...`, "INVALID_YAML", error));
  return ok(parseResult.data);
}

export function validateConfig(config: unknown): Result<LightfastConfig, ConfigError> {
  const parseResult = LightfastConfigSchema.safeParse(config);
  if (!parseResult.success) {
    return err(new ConfigError(`...`, "VALIDATION_ERROR", zodError));
  }
  return ok(parseResult.data);
}
```

**Usage example from the JSDoc**:
```ts
result.match(
  (config) => console.log("Loaded config:", config),
  (error) => console.error("Failed to load config:", error.message)
);
```

`neverthrow` is **only a dependency of `@repo/app-config`** — it is not installed globally across the monorepo.

