### Pattern 4: `{ success: true; ... } | { success: false; error: string }` — discriminated union with `success` key

**Found in 4 separate locations:**

**4a. Named interface pairs** — `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/app/(api)/lib/with-api-key-auth.ts:23-37`

```ts
export interface AuthSuccess {
  auth: ApiKeyAuthContext;
  success: true;
}
export interface AuthError {
  error: { code: string; message: string };
  status: number;
  success: false;
}
export type AuthResult = AuthSuccess | AuthError;
```

Same pattern mirrored in `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/app/(api)/lib/with-dual-auth.ts:22-36` with `DualAuthSuccess`, `DualAuthError`, `DualAuthResult`.

**4b. Inline return type** — `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/api/app/src/lib/activity.ts:112-115`

```ts
export async function recordCriticalActivity(
  data: ActivityData
): Promise<
  { success: true; activityId: number } | { success: false; error: string }
> {
  // ...
  return { success: false, error: `Invalid activity data: ...` };
  return { success: true, activityId: result?.id ?? 0 };
  return { success: false, error: parseError(error) };
}
```

A second function at line 212: `Promise<{ success: true } | { success: false; error: string }>`.

**4c. Local `ValidationResult<T>` interface** — `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/packages/app-providers/src/runtime/validation.ts:4-8`

```ts
interface ValidationResult<T> {
  data?: T;
  errors?: string[];
  success: boolean;
}
// wraps Zod safeParse output
return { success: true, data: result.data };
return { success: false, errors: [...] };
```

